I submitted 6 Hymenophyllum wrightii sequences to genbank using the online BankIt tool.  I submitted the sequences for rbcL and trnS-rps4 from

  * 8338 (Kruzof Island, Alaska),
  * 08011 (Mearas Island, British Columbia), and
  * 08013 (Shi-Shi Trail, Washington).

Sequences for each marker are identical in all 3 taxa (except minor length differences), so I only submitted one from each region (AK, BC, WA) instead of submitting all of my sequences.

# Files Submitted:

## Hwrightii\_sequences\_for_genbank.fasta

~~~
>Seq1 [organism=Hymenophyllum wrightii] Hymenophyllum wrightii chloroplast rbcL gene for ribulose-1,5-bisphosphate carboxylase/oxygenase large subunit, partial cds, Collection 8338, Kruzof Island, Alaska

>Seq2 [organism=Hymenophyllum wrightii] Hymenophyllum wrightii chloroplast rbcL gene for ribulose-1,5-bisphosphate carboxylase/oxygenase large subunit, partial cds, Collection 08011, Mearas Island, British Columbia

>Seq3 [organism=Hymenophyllum wrightii] Hymenophyllum wrightii chloroplast rbcL gene for ribulose-1,5-bisphosphate carboxylase/oxygenase large subunit, partial cds, Collection 08013 Shi-Shi Trail, Washington

>Seq4 [organism=Hymenophyllum wrightii] Hymenophyllum wrightii small ribosomal protein 4 gene and rps4-trnS intergenic spacer, partial sequence, chloroplast, Collection 8338, Kruzof Island, Alaska

>Seq5 [organism=Hymenophyllum wrightii] Hymenophyllum wrightii small ribosomal protein 4 gene and rps4-trnS intergenic spacer, partial sequence, chloroplast, Collection 08011, Mearas Island, British Columbia

>Seq6 [organism=Hymenophyllum wrightii] Hymenophyllum wrightii small ribosomal protein 4 gene and rps4-trnS intergenic spacer, partial sequence, chloroplast, Collection 08013 Shi-Shi Trail, Washington

~~~

>Your Submission ID is **1474050**. This is _not_ an accession number. GenBank accession numbers will be assigned to your submissions and sent to you by email within two working days, unless there are issues with your submission that we must ask you to explain first. If you have any questions or corrections regarding your submissions before you receive these, be sure to refer this Submission ID in your email.

>Your submission data have been sent to GenBank. For each complete sequence submission, you will receive the following at the email address you provided:

>  1. an automatic reply confirming our receipt of your submissions;
>  2. GenBank accession numbers (within two working days); and
>  3. the final GenBank records, processed by the GenBank Annotation staff and incorporating the information you have provided for you to review before they are released to the public database.

>If you do not receive this information from us by email within the time frame indicated, please send an inquiry to <gb-admin@ncbi.nlm.nih.gov> and be sure to include the Submission ID and the email address used in your submission.
